title: Ok. Pulled a proof of the Holy Carp block. It printed well but the block needs some cleanup. A few areas looked off and there's some high areas picking up ink around the edges of the block. When I print this thing for real, I will make a video, because the process is so bananas it has to be seen! The block is inked, then double-sided TAPED to the press bed. I'm using a stiff mat board and no blankets when it runs through the press.... Completely nuts. It's all because of the etching press and some technical issues but I figured it all out! DIY everyday over here! Probably printing the edition of these next week. Finally gettin' shit done around here!
